  <description type="morphology">Stems viny, to 3 m, glabrous or sparsely to moderately pilose-pubescent, denser at
        nodes. Leaf blade 1-2-pinnate or rarely a few simple or 3-foliolate; leaflets 4-10 plus
        additional ± tendril-like terminal leaflet, usually lanceolate to ovate, occasionally
        linear, unlobed or proximally 3-5-lobed, (1.5-)3-10 × (0.1-)0.4-4(-5) cm, thin, not
        conspicuously reticulate; surfaces glabrous, not glaucous. Inflorescences terminal,
        1-flowered; bracts absent. Flowers bell-shaped; sepals distally strongly spreading to
        recurved, violet-blue, lanceolate, 2.5-5 cm, margins proximally thick and tomentose,
        distally broadly expanded, 2-6 mm wide, thin, crispate, less conspicuously tomentose than
        proximal portion, or glabrate, tips acuminate, abaxially glabrous. Achenes: bodies
        appressed-puberulent; beak 2-3.5 cm, appressed-puberulent. 2n = 16.</description>
