  <discussion>Clematis crispa is highly variable in leaflet width, and conspicuous variation may
        occur on a single plant (R.O. Erickson 1943); no discontinuity or geographic correlation
        exists that would permit the recognition of varieties. The dilated, petaloid sepal tips and
        thin, crispate, broadly expanded sepal margins are diagnostic for this species.</discussion>
